## 6. Edge Cases Reference

| Situation | Handling |
|---|---|
| Model with only relation fields | Interface renders as `export interface M {}`, client still generates all 5 methods |
| Model with no `@id` field (composite `@@id`) | `getIdType` returns `{ type: 'unknown', hasId: false }`. `create` uses full interface type. JSDoc warning emitted in class. |
| Optional scalar field (`String?`) | Type is `string \| null`. Interface property is always present (no `?` syntax). |
| Required list field (`String[]`) | Type is `Array<string>`. |
| Optional list field (`String[]?` — uncommon) | Type is `Array<string> \| null`. |
| Enum field in interface | Rendered with the enum name as TS type (e.g., `role: Role`). |
| Empty enum | Renders as `export type E = never`. |
| `Decimal` field | Rendered as `string`. BigInt is `bigint`. |
| `Json` field | Rendered as `unknown`. Callers must cast. |
| `Bytes` field | Rendered as `string` (Base64 convention). |
| `DateTime` field | Rendered as `string` (ISO 8601 convention over HTTP). |
| `Unsupported` field | Skipped silently. |
| Model name starting with lowercase | Interface and class use the DMMF model name verbatim (Prisma guarantees PascalCase model names). |
| `baseUrl` not configured in schema | Defaults to `'/api'` in the generated constructor. |
| Output directory does not exist | `fs.mkdir(outputDir, { recursive: true })` creates it. |
| No output path specified in schema | `generate-client.ts` throws with a helpful error message. |
| Multiple models | Each gets its own interface, client class, and a property on `RestApiClient`. |
| No models in schema | File is still generated with just the header and an empty `RestApiClient {}`. |
| No enums in schema | The Enums section is omitted from the file entirely. |

