## 8. Implementation Sequencing

The files should be created/modified in this order to avoid broken states at each step:

1. Create all new files in `packages/client-generator-rest-api/` first (Steps 1–10). This can be done in any order within the new package since there are no cross-package dependencies yet.
2. Modify `tsconfig.build.bundle.json` (Step 11) — no code dependencies, just enables IDE support.
3. Modify `packages/client-generator-registry/package.json` (Step 12) — adds the dependency declaration.
4. Run `pnpm install` (workspace link) to register the new package.
5. Modify `packages/client-generator-registry/src/default.ts` (Step 13) — the import now resolves because Step 4 linked the package.
6. Modify `packages/client-generator-registry/src/default.test.ts` (Step 14) — update the snapshot after Step 5.
7. Build the new package with `pnpm --filter @prisma/client-generator-rest-api build` to verify the build pipeline.
8. Run tests: `pnpm --filter @prisma/client-generator-rest-api test` then `pnpm --filter @prisma/client-generator-registry test`.

